---
/**
 * Static website terms for public information and project enquiries.
 *
 * Project-specific commercial obligations remain in signed proposals and
 * statements of work; this page does not fabricate prices, refunds, service
 * levels, ownership transfers, or dispute venues that are not evidenced.
 */
import LegalPageShell from "../../components/content/LegalPageShell.astro";
import { LEGAL_CONTACT_EMAIL } from "../../data/contact-channels";

export const prerender = true;

const lastUpdated = "13 July 2026";
const toc = [
  { id: "acceptance", label: "Using this website" },
  { id: "information", label: "Information, not engagement" },
  { id: "enquiries", label: "Project enquiries" },
  { id: "agreements", label: "Proposals and project terms" },
  { id: "intellectual-property", label: "Intellectual property" },
  { id: "conduct", label: "Acceptable use" },
  { id: "third-parties", label: "Third-party services" },
  { id: "availability", label: "Availability and disclaimers" },
  { id: "liability", label: "Responsibility and liability" },
  { id: "law", label: "Law, changes, and contact" },
] as const;
---

<LegalPageShell
  title="Website terms"
  description="Terms for using the Ken Arhin Labs public website, viewing its materials, and sending a project enquiry."
  documentCode="TRM-01"
  documentLabel="Terms"
  lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
  summary="These terms govern the public website and project-enquiry channels. Browsing the site or sending a message does not create a client engagement; project scope, fees, ownership, hosting, support, and risk belong in a separately accepted proposal or statement of work."
  reviewNote="Obtain qualified legal review of the applicable-law, disclaimer, and liability wording before publication. The site currently does not complete purchases or take payments, so do not add generic refund language without a real commercial flow."
  toc={toc}
  visualStages={["Use the website", "Start a conversation", "Agree project terms"]}
>
  <h2 id="acceptance" tabindex="-1">1. Using this website</h2>
  <p>
    These terms apply when you access or use <strong>kenarhinlabs.com</strong> and its public pages,
    materials, contact form, and installable progressive web app features. If you do not agree to
    these terms, do not use the website or submit information through it.
  </p>
  <p>
    The website is operated by Ken Arhin Labs, an independent digital systems business serving a
    global audience. It is a public information and enquiry surface, not a customer account,
    payment portal, self-service hosting platform, or automatically contracting marketplace.
  </p>

  <h2 id="information" tabindex="-1">2. Information, not professional engagement</h2>
  <p>
    The website describes capabilities, working methods, technology choices, selected work, and
    future directions. This material is general information. It is not legal, financial, security,
    compliance, investment, or other regulated professional advice, and it is not a promise that a
    particular technology or approach is suitable for your situation.
  </p>
  <p>
    Examples, diagrams, availability statements, and development fixtures can change as the site
    and services develop. You should confirm the scope, assumptions, dependencies, and current
    status that matter to your decision before relying on them.
  </p>

  <h2 id="enquiries" tabindex="-1">3. Project enquiries do not create a client relationship</h2>
  <p>
    Sending a contact form, email, direct message, or other enquiry invites a conversation only. It
    does not require Ken Arhin Labs to accept work, reserve availability, provide advice, keep an
    idea exclusively confidential, or deliver any service. A client relationship begins only when
    the parties accept a separate written agreement in the manner stated in that agreement.
  </p>
  <p>
    Submit only information you are authorised to share. Do not send passwords, production
    credentials, payment-card information, regulated personal data, or confidential source code
    before an appropriate secure channel and confidentiality arrangement have been agreed.
  </p>
  <p>
    You remain responsible for the accuracy of your enquiry and for obtaining permission to share
    information belonging to another person or organisation. We may use submitted information to
    assess fit, ask follow-up questions, respond, protect the service, and prepare a possible
    proposal, subject to the <a href="/legal/privacy">privacy notice</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="agreements" tabindex="-1">4. Proposals, statements of work, and project terms</h2>
  <p>
    Any proposal, estimate, statement of work, order, or service agreement accepted for a project
    should state the commercial and delivery terms that actually apply. Depending on the project,
    those terms may include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>scope, deliverables, assumptions, exclusions, milestones, and acceptance;</li>
    <li>fees, taxes, provider costs, payment timing, and the effect of late payment;</li>
    <li>client responsibilities, access, approvals, content, and change control;</li>
    <li>ownership and licences for pre-existing materials, deliverables, and third-party assets;</li>
    <li>hosting, domains, data, backups, monitoring, security, support, and service levels;</li>
    <li>privacy, confidentiality, warranties, liability allocation, and termination; and</li>
    <li>handoff, account ownership, portability, exit assistance, and dispute handling.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The accepted project agreement controls if it conflicts with these website terms on a
    project-specific matter. The public website does not currently complete purchases or take
    payments, so cancellation, return, refund, renewal, and subscription terms must be supplied in
    the relevant accepted agreement rather than inferred from this page.
  </p>

  <h2 id="intellectual-property" tabindex="-1">5. Intellectual property and permitted use</h2>
  <p>
    Unless a page says otherwise, Ken Arhin Labs or its licensors retain rights in the website's
    authored text, brand assets, layouts, diagrams, code presentation, and other original material.
    Third-party technology and social marks belong to their respective owners and are shown for
    identification; their appearance does not imply endorsement or partnership.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may view, link to, and make reasonable personal or internal-business use of publicly
    available pages. You may not, without permission or another lawful basis, reproduce a
    substantial part of the site for commercial use, remove rights notices, impersonate the brand,
    misrepresent affiliation, resell materials, or use the site in a way that infringes another
    person's rights.
  </p>
  <p>
    Ownership and permitted use of client deliverables, reusable tools, licensed software, and
    client-supplied materials are determined by the relevant project agreement, not by this page.
  </p>

  <h2 id="conduct" tabindex="-1">6. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You must not use the website or its enquiry channels to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>break applicable law or encourage unlawful activity;</li>
    <li>submit malicious code, automated abuse, spam, or deceptive requests;</li>
    <li>probe, bypass, disrupt, overload, or gain unauthorised access to systems or data;</li>
    <li>infringe privacy, confidentiality, intellectual-property, or other legal rights;</li>
    <li>misrepresent your identity, authority, or relationship with another party; or</li>
    <li>interfere with another visitor's safe and ordinary use of the site.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may restrict requests or access where reasonably necessary to protect people, the website,
    its providers, or legal rights. Project termination, suspension, data return, and transition
    obligations are governed by the applicable signed project agreement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="third-parties" tabindex="-1">7. Third-party services, hosting, and links</h2>
  <p>
    The website may identify or link to cloud, database, AI, development, social, and communication
    platforms. Those services are operated under their own terms, availability, security, pricing,
    and privacy practices. A link or technology mark is not a warranty or endorsement.
  </p>
  <p>
    Ken Arhin Labs can currently design, deploy, and manage client systems using established
    infrastructure providers. Provider selection, account and billing ownership, regions, domains,
    access, backups, monitoring, incident response, support, portability, and exit procedures must
    be agreed for each project. The planned Ken Arhin Labs hosting platform is not yet a live
    self-service product.
  </p>
  <p>
    We are not responsible for the content or independent operation of an external site simply
    because this website links to it. Review the external provider's terms before relying on it.
  </p>

  <h2 id="availability" tabindex="-1">8. Availability and disclaimers</h2>
  <p>
    We aim to keep the public site useful and accurate, but it may be interrupted, cached, delayed,
    incomplete, or unavailable. Previously visited PWA pages may be shown offline and may not
    reflect the newest content, availability, or service status.
  </p>
  <p>
    To the extent permitted by applicable law, the public site and its general information are
    provided without a promise that they will be uninterrupted, error-free, complete, secure for
    every purpose, or suitable for your particular needs. Nothing in these terms limits a specific
    written warranty expressly included in an accepted project agreement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="liability" tabindex="-1">9. Responsibility and liability</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for how you use public information and for maintaining appropriate copies,
    security, permissions, and professional advice for your own systems. To the extent permitted by
    applicable law, Ken Arhin Labs is not responsible under these website terms for indirect or
    consequential loss arising only from use of, inability to use, or reliance on the public site
    or an independently operated third-party service.
  </p>
  <p>
    This wording does not exclude or restrict liability that applicable law does not allow to be
    excluded or restricted. Liability, remedies, service levels, and risk allocation for paid
    client work belong in the accepted project agreement. This section requires qualified legal
    review before the page is treated as final.
  </p>

  <h2 id="law" tabindex="-1">10. Applicable law, changes, and contact</h2>
  <p>
    These website terms are interpreted under applicable law while preserving mandatory rights
    that may apply to a visitor where they live. Any project-specific governing law, forum,
    escalation, mediation, or other dispute process must be stated in the accepted project
    agreement; this page does not impose an exclusive court or venue.
  </p>
  <p>
    We may update these terms as the public website and its services change. The last-updated date
    identifies the current draft. Continued use after a revised version is published applies to
    later use of the website, but it does not silently rewrite an already accepted project
    agreement.
  </p>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms can be sent to{" "}
    <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{LEGAL_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>. General project
    enquiries can be raised through the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</LegalPageShell>
